description.narrative: Children at risk of, or exposed to violence, exploitation and abuse are increasingly able to access and benefit from higher quality core child protection and gender based violence in emergency and non-emergency settings by 2018, which contributes to Child Protection And Emergencies, Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Violence, Exploitation And Abuse. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: South Sudanese children and adolescents at risk of or exposed to violence, exploitation and abuse have their risk reduced, mitigated and where possible, their safety, dignity and health restored by 2018.

description.narrative: UNICEF and partners supported the child protection in emergency response, reaching 736,740 individuals including 470,519 children and 266,221 adults with critical child protection services. Specific areas of support included family tracing and reunification, psycho-social support, mine-risk education, gender-based violence and reintegration of children from armed forces and armed groups. | Status:Partially Met | As-of Date:31/12/2018
